title: Saving Web page as pdf problem
content:
I use Firefox mostly so it's a concern. MS O365 Support tested this problem with MS Edge so it is not a problem with another browser or MS O365. Thus I am keying in to Mozilla.

I have three One Drives: One Personal and Two Business, each Drive has a Unique Name. When I Save as PDF using Firefox browser, I expect to see all three as they are labeled in my Windows Explorer. Since I use mostly Firefox, I believe in the past, for years, I saw all three One Drives as labeled. However just today, I am saving a web page as a PDF to one of the Business One Drives. Yet that Business One Drive picked up the name of the personal One Drive exactly, making it confusing. The content of the renamed One Drive has not changed, the properties has not changed, only the name changed.

Some facts: My Firefox user name email is the same as my MS personal account email. It is the only common denominator I can think of. Firefox is Up to Date with Version 106.0.5

I have uploaded screen shots 1. Drives as seen in Windows Explorer and 2. Drives as seen when saving a web page as a PDF using Firefox.

Any idea what is the cause and fix?

Thank you so much! Robert

content: Yesterday, I could reach up and access a pull-down bookmarks menu. Today, in that same place were several links to places I never go, such as the homepages for Bing(?), Google(?) and Yahoo(?), all of which I have deleted. title: My internet fluctuates constantly while using the Firefox browser.
content:
Hello.

My internet fluctuates constantly while using the Firefox browser. It uses full capacity for 5 seconds, then uses almost 1 mbps internet for the next 5 seconds, then uses full capacity for 5 seconds and so on. I tried a lot of things but it didn't work. I have 100 Mbps internet and connect with 5GHz WI-FI.

Things I've tried:

-Reset Firefox -Run Firefox in troubleshooting mode -Turn off Anti-Virus and Adguard Ad Blocker -DNS flush -Formatting the computer

I don't have such internet fluctuation problem when using it in Microsoft Edge browser. It works seamlessly.

Apart from this, there is another situation that I encountered once, as long as I do not format the computer on which I installed Firefox, this internet fluctuation occurs constantly.

title: İnternet hızında dalgalanma sorunu
content:
Merhaba.

Firefox tarayıcısını kullanırken internetim sürekli dalgalanıyor. 5 saniye boyunca tam kapasite kullanırken, bundan sonraki 5 saniyede nereyese 1 mbps internet kullanıyor, sonra tekrar 5 saniye boyunca tam kapasite kullanıyor ve böyle devam ediyor. Çok şey denedim ama bir türlü düzelmedi. 100 Mbps internetim var ve 5GHz WI-FI ile bağlantı kuruyorum.

Denediğim şeyler:

-Firefox'u sıfırlama -Firefox'u sorun giderme modunda çalıştırma -Anti-Virus ve Adguard Reklam Engelleyici'yi kapatma -DNS flush -Bilgisayara format atma

Microsoft Edge tarayıcısında kullanırken böyle bir dalgalanma problemim yok. Sıkıntısız bir şekilde çalışıyor.

Bunun yanında buna sadece 1 kere denk geldim. Firefox kurduğum bilgisayara format atmadığım sürece bu internet dalgalanması sürekli meydana geliyor.
creator: kadiremre98

title: Firefox 'forgets' bookmark changes & more on closing
content: Hello For years now my Firefox has lost any new bookmarks, and edits to existing ones, once closed. For some reason on opening it always has just 4 bookmarks (on the bookmarks toolbar) from ages ago but no new ones from the previous session, nor any edits to the few old ones. It would be helpful if clicking Save actually did that. Recently I have been adding DuckDuckGo Privacy Essentials to my few extensions (as encouraged by Firefox) but that also disappears completely overnight. Fortunately the longer-standing add-ons are so far staying in place. However, the LastPass password manager now drops the master password just a few minutes after logging in, over and over again. There have been periods in past years when that password has been dropped some while after logging in but managed to stick after being entered just once more; but that hasn't been happening for quite a while until this new behaviour started a week or so ago. This problem does not happen in the Opera browser which I've started using again so I have to assume it is a Firefox issue not a LastPass one. I don't know if it's relevant but I do clear all cookie & site data before closing Firefox and it is set to never remember history. I would much prefer to continue using Firefox but it just takes too much effort these days! Firefox 106.0.5 64bit currently; Win10 (21H2 auto-updated. Thank you.

title: Linux o Android App per Chromebook
content: Buongiorno, ho un Chromebook Lenovo IdeaPad Flex 3 basato su Celeron N4500 con 8GB di RAM. Devo decidere se intallare Firefox in versione Linux oppure Android. A parte le differenze di funzionalità, quale versione è più veloce e leggera su Chrome OS del Chromebook? Grazie e saluti, Stefano

title: A window with all its tabs dissappeared, won't show on restart...

I found firefox old backups and sessions folder but none of the session restore files are dated, won't open and won't restore. I wish there was a straight-forward path to restore "my sessions" when issues develop. Just show me where the file path > where the files are > and what to click. Thank you.
